<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-06-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1">
                    <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-chapter-head">[Argument.]</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-06-10">June
                                    10, 1872</date>.</hi>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> We have the honor to hand you herewith the
                        argument prepared by us as counsel of the United States, in order that, in
                        pursuance of Article V of the treaty of Washington, it may be presented in
                        their behalf to the tribunal of arbitration constituted by that treaty.</p>
                    <p>We have the honor, sir, to be your obedient servants,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>C. CUSHING.</signed>
                        <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                        <signed>M. E. WAITE.</signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">J. C. Bancroft Davis,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">Agent of the United States.</hi></p>
                    </postscript>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>